One-sentence impressions of songs from music nerds. Most recent nerdlets:
"In The Cold, Cold Night" is sung by Meg White (drummer), very bluesy, simple guitar riff.
"Seven Nation Army" is Probably the White Stripes biggest hit. Awesome slide guitar.
"Blue Orchid" is a classic for any White Stripes fan. Straightforward drums and falsetto vocals.
"Fell In Love With A Girl" is Often recognized as one of the songs that put The White Stripes on the map.
"Rich Kid Blues" is the story of my life, wonderful guitar and tentitive lyrics
"See The Sky About To Rain" is "see the sky About to rain" is a song have heartly touching lyrics and tell be in a hope.
"Walk On" is "walk on" is very good at it phylosiphy of life just move on in life
"Dominated Love Slave" is not exactly the best Tre song, but it fits the album.
"Ambulance Blues" is more than just 'pissing in the wind' (love singing that!). The 'liar' in the song is Richard Nixon.
